rences were cultivated by state actors so as to support a set of right-wing positions including anti-communism, the Jim Crow status quo, and limited taxation and regulation.Faith in Freedom is a pioneering work of American religious history. By assessing the ideas, policies, and actions of three US Presidents and their White House staff, Polk sheds light on the origins of the ideological, religious, and partisan divides that describe the American polity today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aChristianity and politicszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aCold WarxPropaganda. 0aPropaganda, AmericanxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xPropaganda. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aReligious Studies. 4aU.S. History. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aCold War Religion, American Civil Religion, religion in post war America, WWII and religion, religion war and politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150175923940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501759239423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501759239/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aEB